        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>nasal</p><ul><li>adj. 鼻的；带有鼻音的</li></ul><p>mite</p><ul><li>螨虫</li><li>a mite ~</li><li>poor little mite</li></ul><p>inferior</p><ul><li>No body is inferior to you here.</li><li>No inferior products should be allowed to pass.</li></ul><p>rejoice</p><ul><li>(~ at/in/over) The motor industry is rejoicing at the cut in car tax.</li><li>When the war ended, people finally had cause to rejoice.</li></ul><p>preliminary</p><ul><li>(n.) I will skip the usual preliminaries, and come straight to the point.</li><li>(adj.) After a few preliminary remarks he announced the winners.</li></ul><p>conscious</p><ul><li>(adj.) be ~ of (doing) sth. She is acutely conscious of the severeness of the problem.</li></ul><p>pride and prejudice</p><p>bride and groom</p><p>predecessor and successor</p><p>relate </p><ul><li>relate a tail story.(narrate)</li></ul><p>relative</p><ul><li>n. 亲戚</li><li>adj. 相对的，相关的 (~ to)</li></ul><p>relativity</p><ul><li>n. 相关性</li></ul><p>relevant</p><ul><li>(irrelevant) 紧密相关的，切题的</li><li>These comments are not directly relevant to this inquiry.</li><li>有价值的，有意义的（relevance）</li><li>I don’t see the relevance of your question.</li></ul><p>overlook</p><ul><li>She has been overlooked for promotion several times.</li><li>We could not afford to overlook such a serious offense.</li><li>a restaurant overlooking the lake.</li></ul><p>overseas /~si:z/</p><ul><li>adj. 海外的 ~ development/markets</li><li>adv. to work overseas.</li></ul><p>apt</p><ul><li>an apt description/comment</li><li>be apt to do sth. Babies are apt to put objects into their mouths.</li></ul><p>mock</p><ul><li>v. 嘲笑</li><li>adj. 虚假的</li><li>adj. 模拟的，模仿的</li></ul><p>premier</p><ul><li>n. 总理</li><li>adj. 最好的，最重要的</li></ul><p>displace</p><ul><li>Gradually, factory workers have been displaced by machines.</li><li>Around 10,000 people have been displaced by the continuous  fighting.</li></ul><p>He is a genius and invented a lot of ingenious devices.</p>]]></content>
      
      
